# Auto-deploy on contract changes

When you modify any Solidity file under `packages/contracts/contracts/` (including `lib/Categories.sol`):

1. Run tests: `cd packages/contracts && npm test`
2. If tests pass, deploy without asking the user:
   `cd packages/contracts && npm run deploy:sepolia`
3. Update `packages/web/.env.local` -> `NEXT_PUBLIC_SALARY_FHE_ADDRESS` with the new address from deploy output (deploy script also writes `packages/web/src/abi/deployment.json`).
4. Verify on Etherscan:
   `cd packages/contracts && npx hardhat verify --network sepolia <ADDRESS>`
5. Briefly tell the user the new address and Etherscan link.

Do not ask for permission to deploy. Skip deploy only if tests fail or `.env` lacks `PRIVATE_KEY` / deployer has zero balance (report blocker instead).

Never print or commit private keys.
